  "text": "Given the association of RT and OS, we hypothesized that delivering a higher BED would result in improved [CITATION_1] . One-year, 3-year, and 5-year OS were 64%, 29%, and 19%, respectively, for those who were treated with a BED ≥ 72 Gy 10 compared to 49%, 20%, and 13% for those who received BED < 72 Gy 10 ( Figure 4 , HR: 0.78, 95% CI: 0.72-0.85, log-rank P < .001).",
